              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{7,"682"`l times  {  {1 "." "77"` ital "kg"}  over  {1`l} } ="13","597"` ital "kg"} {}</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id1169113389734"/>
        <para id="id1169119380244">Next, the crew went about determining the weight of fuel that would need to be transferred to the fuel tanks. They found this to be 8,703 kilograms, as shown in the differencing operation below</para>
        <equation id="id1169136831851">
          <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mtext>22</m:mtext>
                      <m:mi>,</m:mi>
                      <m:mtext>300</m:mtext>
                      <m:mi/>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mtext>kg</m:mtext>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo>
                        <m:mtext>13</m:mtext>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mi>,</m:mi>
                      <m:mtext>597</m:mtext>
                      <m:mi/>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                          <m:mrow>
                            <m:mtext>kg</m:mtext>
                          </m:mrow>
                        </m:mstyle>
                        <m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo>
                        <m:mn>8,</m:mn>
                      </m:mrow>
                      <m:mtext>703</m:mtext>
                      <m:mi/>
                      <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mtext>kg</m:mtext>
                        </m:mrow>
                      </m:mstyle>
                    </m:mrow>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mstyle>
                <m:mrow/>
              </m:mrow>
              <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"22","300"` ital "kg" - "13","597"` ital "kg"=8,"703"` ital "kg"} {}</m:annotation>
            </m:semantics>
          </m:math>
        </equation>
        <para id="id1169129542012">Finally, the volume of fuel in liters that needed to be transferred to the fuel tanks before departure for Edmundton was calculated. Once again, the erroroneous conversion factor was used as shown below</para>
        <equation id="id1169130615013">
          <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
            <m:semantics>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mstyle fontsize="12pt">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mrow>
                      <m:mn>8,</m:mn>
                      <m:mtext>703</m:mtext>
                      <m:mi/>
                      <m:mrow>
                        <m:mrow>
                          <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                            <m:mrow>
                              <m:mtext>kg</m:mtext>
                            </m:mrow>
                          </m:mstyle>
                          <m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo>
